title: Spain at risk of political gridlock after conservative win falls short of toppling PM
description: Spain appears headed for political gridlock after Sunday’s  national elections left parties on both the right and left without a clear path to a new government.

title: Crowds of protesters march to Jerusalem in effort to stop Netanyahu’s plan to weaken Supreme Court
description: Thousands of protesters marched to Jerusalem over the weekend in an effort to stop Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s plan to weaken the Supreme Court. NBC News’ Raf Sanchez has the latest.

title: Historic Ukrainian cathedral damaged in Russian missile strikes
description: The Spaso-Preobrazhenskyi Cathedral, or Transfiguration Cathedral, was severely damaged during a Russian missile attack on the Ukrainian port city of Odesa that killed one person and injured several others.

title: Thousands forced to flee as wildfire rages on Greek island of Rhodes
description: A wildfire raging on the Greek island of Rhodes forced thousands to shelter in schools and stadiums after they were evacuated from coastal villages and resorts.

title: Russian missile strikes on Odesa kills 1 and damages historic cathedral
description: Russian missile strikes on the port city of Odesa left at least one person dead and 19 injured, and damaged important buildings in the historic city center/

title: The 1975 cancels shows after band’s same-sex kiss controversy
description: British pop rock band The 1975 said Sunday it was canceling shows in the wake of the band’s lead singer kissing a male bandmate during their performance.

title: Israel’s Netanyahu taken to hospital for heart procedure Saturday night
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said early Sunday that he was going to the hospital for an emergency procedure to receive a pacemaker, but he vowed to press ahead with his controversial judicial overhaul plan.
